                  {
                    "text": "The “Maternal Nutrition” scheme is a component under the \"Mukhyamantri Sampoorna Pushti Yojana (MSPY)\" scheme, introduced by the Department of Women & Child Development, Government of Odisha. The scheme aims to provide supplementary Take Home Ration (THR) in the form of nutrient-rich food products to pregnant women and lactating mothers across the state. Additionally, essential services such as antenatal care (ANC) check-ups during Mamata Diwas, immunisation, and IFA and calcium supplementation are also provided. The scheme has been implemented for a five-year period, commencing from FY 2023-24 to FY 2027-28."
